Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BootStrapNode
    Defines the operations of the BootStrapNodeImpl such as joins and departures.
    ChordNode
    Defines the standard operations as stated in the original Chord paper with methods such as find_successor and fix_fingers.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BootStrapNodeImpl
    This class serves as the starting point for the BootStrap server and has functions to assist in node joins and departure while also serves the purpose of collecting metrics for the improvements made.
    ChordNodeImpl
    The standard chord node of the network,implements the ChordNode interface.
    ChordNodeImplTest
    Basic test suite with CRUD operations.Run by MyTestRunner.
    FingerTableEntry
    Used to represent contents of the finger table used by each ChordNodeImpl.
    ImageCanvas
    This class is used to distribute images over the network.
    MyTestRunner
    The test runner used to run the ChordNodeImplTest.
    NodeInfo
    Contains info about the nodes of the network such as the node ip,port and id.
    Result
    Represents the response received by various operations in the chord network.
